response.question: Q2: What is the time complexity of linear search?
response.correct_answer: The time complexity of linear search is O(n). This is because in the worst-case scenario, the algorithm has to iterate through all 'n' elements of the list to find the target value.
response.feedback: Score: 1.0/1.0. Graded against Reference Key and Assignment Description. The student has correctly identified the time complexity of linear search as O(n).
